-- BP Plans for $1.73 Billion Legal Bill, Financial Times Reports
-- B y   A b i g a i l   M o s e s
-- 2012-02-25T10:49:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-25/bp-plans-for-1-73-billion-legal-bill-financial-times-reports.html
BP Plc (BP)  plans to spend $1.73 billion
on legal and administrative costs from the 2010 Deepwater
Horizon Gulf of Mexico oil spill, the  Financial Times  reported,
citing provisions in the company’s annual report.  That doesn’t include clean-up or compensation costs, and
the company’s accounts put the total cost of the spill at $37.2
billion, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
